Sky view factor (SVF) SVF is the visible sky in a hemisphere centered visible from the ground at a given point (cell in the raster map). It varies significantly with the topography of different regions and is used to account for obstruction of the overlying sky hemisphere by surrounding land surface as an adjustment factor, with regions with lower visibility related to lower LD risk (Zakšek et al. 2011; Bernard et al. 2018). It is defined as:12SVF=1N×∑i=1Ncosβ×cos2βφi+sinβ×cos∅i-α×90-φi-sinφi×cosφi,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
